==Latin==

===Etymology===
{{PIE root|la|bʰer|telh₂}}
A suppletive paradigm consisting of two different roots.

The present stem is from {{inh|la|itc-pro|*ferō}}, from {{inh|la|ine-pro|*bʰéreti||to bear, carry}}, from the root {{m|ine-pro|*bʰer-}}. Cognates include Sanskrit {{m|sa|भरति|tr=bhárati}}, Ancient Greek {{m|grc|φέρω}}, Old English {{m|ang|beran}} (English {{m|en|bear}}).

The perfect stem, originally of {{m|la|tollō}}, is from {{inh|la|itc-pro||*tetolai}}, from {{inh|la|ine-pro|*tetólh₂e||to be holding up}}, from the root {{m|ine-pro|*telh₂-}}. The stem of {{m|la|lātus}} has the same root, reduced from {{inh|la|itc-pro|*tlātos}}, from {{inh|la|ine-pro|*tl̥h₂tós}}. It is cognate with English {{m|en|thole||to endure}}.

